WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:05.403
♪♪

00:05.472 --> 00:07.639
[excited chatter]

00:07.708 --> 00:08.640
Hm.

00:08.709 --> 00:11.710
♪♪

00:16.750 --> 00:18.283
Ah, thank you!

00:18.352 --> 00:19.484
You must be new.

00:19.553 --> 00:20.718
I'm Apple Bloom.

00:20.787 --> 00:22.821
I'm Grand Pear.

00:22.890 --> 00:24.223
Welcome to Ponyville!

00:24.291 --> 00:27.158
You mean, welcome
<i>back</i> to Ponyville!

00:27.227 --> 00:29.260
Grand Pear was
originally from here

00:29.329 --> 00:32.363
before he opened his famous
pear jam store in VanHoover!

00:32.432 --> 00:34.866
Really? Why'd you move back?

00:34.935 --> 00:39.471
I uh, well, I needed
a change of pace.

00:39.540 --> 00:40.705
Ah.

00:40.774 --> 00:41.806
[chomp]

00:41.875 --> 00:43.174
This is delicious!

00:43.243 --> 00:45.143
[chomp]

00:45.212 --> 00:46.744
I can't believe I've
gone my whole life

00:46.813 --> 00:48.146
without ever having this!

00:48.215 --> 00:49.447
Glad you like it.

00:49.516 --> 00:50.648
How much?

00:50.717 --> 00:52.617
Nah.

00:52.686 --> 00:55.620
Wow, thanks, Mr.
Grand Pear, sir!

00:55.689 --> 00:58.456
It was real nice meetin' you!

00:58.525 --> 01:01.460
[chatter]

01:05.866 --> 01:07.499
Glad you're back, sugar cube!

01:07.568 --> 01:10.468
Just in time for
breakfast-for-dinner!

01:10.537 --> 01:13.372
I got the perfect topper for
flapjacks at the market today!

01:15.275 --> 01:15.874
[gasp]

01:15.943 --> 01:17.509
PEAR JAM?

01:17.578 --> 01:19.210
What were you thinking?

01:19.279 --> 01:19.878
[door closes]

01:19.947 --> 01:21.746
[tense music]

01:21.815 --> 01:22.748
Quick, hide it!

01:26.653 --> 01:27.719
Huh?

01:30.857 --> 01:34.325
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:34.394 --> 01:36.261
<i>♪ Aaaahhh ♪</i>

01:36.330 --> 01:37.930
<i>♪ My little Pony ♪</i>

01:37.998 --> 01:40.732
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:40.801 --> 01:42.501
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

01:42.569 --> 01:45.203
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:45.272 --> 01:47.005
<i>♪ Big adventure! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun ♪</i>

01:47.074 --> 01:48.840
<i>♪ A beautiful heart! ♪ ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

01:48.909 --> 01:51.576
<i>♪ Sharing kindness ♪</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat ♪</i>

01:51.645 --> 01:53.578
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

01:53.647 --> 01:55.713
<i>♪ To have my little pony ♪</i>

01:55.782 --> 01:59.217
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

01:59.286 --> 02:01.587
♪♪

02:06.593 --> 02:08.359
♪♪

02:08.428 --> 02:09.827
What's the big deal?

02:09.896 --> 02:11.663
It's just Pear Jam!

02:11.732 --> 02:13.231
The big deal
is that there

02:13.300 --> 02:14.465
is a long-
standing feud

02:14.534 --> 02:16.301
between the Apples
and the Pears!

02:16.370 --> 02:18.303
Yeeup!

02:18.372 --> 02:19.504
Why?

02:19.573 --> 02:20.939
Why?

02:21.008 --> 02:24.275
Well, uh, actually
I'm not really sure.

02:24.344 --> 02:25.877
You have any idea, Big Mac?

02:25.946 --> 02:28.546
Uuuuh, nope.

02:28.615 --> 02:30.415
Then I guess we
should ask Granny?

02:30.484 --> 02:31.517
Ask me what?

02:33.820 --> 02:35.987
Uh, what goes better with
apple fritter flapjacks,

02:36.056 --> 02:37.855
caramel syrup or praline?

02:37.924 --> 02:39.491
Praline!

02:41.428 --> 02:43.995
Oh ho ho, that smells
great, Applejack!

02:44.064 --> 02:45.897
I'm gonna wash
up for supper.

02:45.966 --> 02:47.932
Be right back.

02:48.001 --> 02:48.833
[door closes]

02:48.902 --> 02:49.934
[sigh]

02:50.003 --> 02:51.236
Listen, sugar cube.

02:51.304 --> 02:53.938
Anytime Big Mac and I ever
asked Granny about the feud

02:54.007 --> 02:57.342
or the Pears, she'd get so
upset she couldn't talk.

02:57.411 --> 02:58.677
Best not bring it up.

03:00.580 --> 03:03.748
OK. But that Grand Pear
was really nice to me,

03:03.817 --> 03:05.350
even though I'm an Apple.

03:05.419 --> 03:06.784
I wonder what happened.

03:06.853 --> 03:07.952
Me too.

03:08.021 --> 03:10.722
But if we can't ask Granny,
I don't know who--

03:10.791 --> 03:13.591
We can ask Goldie Delicious!

03:13.660 --> 03:17.328
If anypony knows about the
feud, it's the family historian!

03:17.397 --> 03:19.497
I'm in! Whaddya
say, Big Mac?

03:19.566 --> 03:21.566
Sibling trip first
thing tomorrow?

03:21.635 --> 03:22.801
Yeeup!

03:26.707 --> 03:27.739
[knock]

03:27.808 --> 03:30.341
[yowling cats]

03:30.410 --> 03:31.944
[crash]

03:37.117 --> 03:39.817
Now that's how you
make an entrance.

03:39.886 --> 03:41.185
Or is it an exit?

03:41.254 --> 03:44.689
Well, anyway, it's so
wonderful to see you three!

03:44.758 --> 03:47.725
To what do I owe
the pleasure?

03:47.794 --> 03:51.362
Well, Goldie, we were hoping you
could tell us about the... uh...

03:51.431 --> 03:53.898
feud with the Apples
and the Pears.

03:53.967 --> 03:56.367
Oh...oh, dear!

03:56.436 --> 03:58.469
Does Granny Smith
know you're here?

03:58.538 --> 03:59.904
No, ma'am.

03:59.973 --> 04:03.641
But I ran into Grand Pear
yesterday and he was real nice.

04:03.710 --> 04:05.810
Maybe the feud was a
misunderstanding or something

04:05.879 --> 04:07.745
and we can fix it?

04:07.814 --> 04:10.948
Hmm. Well, I don't know
about that, little one.

04:11.017 --> 04:12.984
But if it's the
story you're after,

04:13.053 --> 04:15.620
I suppose you have
a right to know.

04:15.689 --> 04:18.356
Let's see here, I got a stack
of books here someplace.

04:18.425 --> 04:21.426
Oh! Apple family history
volume one-thirty-seven.

04:22.696 --> 04:23.661
Here we are!

04:23.730 --> 04:25.396
Feud with the Bears.

04:25.465 --> 04:26.731
I mean Pears.

04:26.800 --> 04:29.067
My eyes ain't what
they used to be.

04:29.136 --> 04:32.103
A long time ago,
Sweet Apple Acres

04:32.172 --> 04:34.806
wasn't the only
farm in Ponyville.

04:34.875 --> 04:37.809
In fact, there was another
one just right next door,

04:39.980 --> 04:41.646
Come and get your apples!

04:41.715 --> 04:43.781
Nothing sweeter than
biting into a crisp apple

04:43.850 --> 04:46.517
on a beautiful fall day.

04:46.586 --> 04:49.554
Unless, of course, you could
bite into a juicy pear!

04:49.623 --> 04:50.922
Please!

04:50.991 --> 04:52.990
Pears are just what happens
when you ain't no good

04:53.059 --> 04:55.126
at farming apples.

04:55.195 --> 04:57.528
Pears are nature's candy!

04:57.597 --> 05:00.064
Apples are sour,

05:00.133 --> 05:01.999
like the expression on
your face right now!

05:02.068 --> 05:03.101
[chuckle]

05:03.170 --> 05:04.836
<i>Goldie: And so it went.</i>

05:04.905 --> 05:07.405
<i>Granny and Grand Pear were</i>
<i>always at each other:</i>

05:07.474 --> 05:08.807
<i>Who was the best farmer?</i>

05:08.875 --> 05:10.408
<i>Who took better</i>
<i>care of their trees?</i>

05:10.477 --> 05:13.911
<i>If Granny read to</i>
<i>her trees at night...</i>

05:13.980 --> 05:17.081
"... And then the little
tree reached its branches

05:17.150 --> 05:20.786
up to the moon and the
moon said good night.

05:22.789 --> 05:25.523
<i>... why then Grand Pear had</i>
<i>special blankets made</i>

05:25.592 --> 05:28.526
<i>for his trees so they</i>
<i>wouldn't get cold.</i>

05:28.595 --> 05:29.727
Good night, trees.

05:29.796 --> 05:30.762
[kiss]

05:30.831 --> 05:32.130
I've got you covered.

05:32.199 --> 05:33.765
Mm hm.

05:33.834 --> 05:34.866
[snarl]

05:38.505 --> 05:41.973
[shouts]

05:42.042 --> 05:45.977
<i>In fact, all the Apples and the</i>
<i>Pears were rivals to the core.</i>

05:49.549 --> 05:51.716
<i>The only Apple and Pear</i>
<i>who ever got along</i>

05:51.785 --> 05:54.852
<i>were Bright Macintosh</i>
<i>and Pear Butter.</i>

05:54.921 --> 05:57.688
Psst.

05:57.757 --> 06:00.425
I'm not supposed
to talk to you.

06:00.494 --> 06:02.727
I'm not supposed to
talk to you either.

06:02.796 --> 06:05.897
My mom says if you hold a
buttercup under your chin,

06:05.966 --> 06:07.432
it'll make your
chin glow.

06:07.501 --> 06:08.699
But it doesn't
work on me.

06:08.768 --> 06:09.735
See?

06:11.104 --> 06:13.037
Does it work on me?

06:13.106 --> 06:14.639
[heartbeat]

06:14.708 --> 06:16.974
It sure does, buttercup.

06:17.043 --> 06:20.878
Buttercup. I
like that name.

06:20.947 --> 06:22.680
<i>Applejack: Wait an</i>
<i>apple pickin' minute!</i>

06:22.749 --> 06:24.916
Bright Mac and Buttercup?

06:24.985 --> 06:27.118
Those are our parents names!

06:27.187 --> 06:28.886
Course, Buttercup was just
the nickname your father

06:28.955 --> 06:30.154
gave your mother.

06:30.223 --> 06:33.691
Pear Butter. Well, that
was her given name.

06:33.760 --> 06:36.627
Are you saying our
mother was a<i> Pear</i> ?

06:36.696 --> 06:37.763
[gasp]

06:41.201 --> 06:43.901
So we are
half-Pear?

06:43.970 --> 06:45.937
I can't
believe it!

06:46.006 --> 06:47.172
How did we
not know?

06:47.241 --> 06:51.042
Well, nopony called your
mother Pear Butter...

06:51.111 --> 06:53.511
And her cutie mark was a
preserve jar but pear butter

06:53.580 --> 06:54.946
don't look too much different
from apple butter...

06:55.015 --> 06:57.014
so no clues there.

06:57.083 --> 07:01.152
Is there anything else you
can tell us about them?

07:01.221 --> 07:03.855
I know they loved
each other very much!

07:03.924 --> 07:06.991
They had that
magical, star-kissed,

07:07.060 --> 07:10.828
other side of a
rainbow kind of love.

07:10.897 --> 07:12.163
You couldn't be
around 'em too long

07:12.232 --> 07:15.132
and not feel a little bit
lighter than air yourself.

07:15.201 --> 07:16.734
[giggle]

07:16.803 --> 07:19.537
Anything else?

07:19.606 --> 07:22.040
I'd need volume one hundred
and thirty-eight for that.

07:23.076 --> 07:24.542
[snarl]

07:24.611 --> 07:25.910
I'm sure I could wrangle it...

07:25.979 --> 07:28.112
in a couple days.

07:28.181 --> 07:29.881
That's all
right, Goldie.

07:29.950 --> 07:31.582
It was nice
just to hear--

07:31.651 --> 07:34.151
Ooh ooh! I just
remembered somethin'!

07:34.220 --> 07:36.120
Your dad and his
buddy, Burnt Oak,

07:36.189 --> 07:39.190
would get in all kinds of
trouble together as colts!

07:39.259 --> 07:40.858
Burnt Oak?

07:40.927 --> 07:42.827
The firewood salespony?

07:42.896 --> 07:44.795
I haven't seen
him in ages.

07:44.864 --> 07:47.265
He and your dad were thick
as thieves back in the day.

07:47.334 --> 07:48.700
Y'all should talk to him.

07:50.904 --> 07:51.969
[crash]

07:52.038 --> 07:52.971
[growl]

07:55.375 --> 07:57.975
Well, well, if it
isn't the Apples!

07:58.044 --> 07:59.777
What can I do for you?

07:59.846 --> 08:01.712
I know you're not
here for firewood.

08:01.781 --> 08:04.916
You've got more trees
than anypony in Ponyville!

08:04.985 --> 08:05.950
You're right.

08:06.019 --> 08:08.019
We're not here for that.

08:08.088 --> 08:10.555
Come to ask
about your dad?

08:10.624 --> 08:12.990
Uh, eeeyup.

08:13.059 --> 08:14.725
I wondered if you might.

08:14.794 --> 08:15.893
I hoped you would.

08:15.962 --> 08:17.228
It's nice to talk about him.

08:17.297 --> 08:19.163
[laugh]

08:19.232 --> 08:20.765
We had a lot of laughs.

08:20.834 --> 08:22.567
In fact, this one time...

08:22.636 --> 08:25.202
<i>... we were racing to see who</i>
<i>could till the fastest</i>

08:25.271 --> 08:27.838
<i>and Bright Mac was</i>
<i>leavin' me in the dust!</i>

08:27.907 --> 08:31.042
<i>He would've won too if he</i>
<i>wasn't so distracted.</i>

08:33.113 --> 08:33.979
Whoa!

08:35.048 --> 08:36.047
[crash]

08:36.116 --> 08:37.549
[splash]

08:42.322 --> 08:43.588
Oh!

08:46.359 --> 08:48.893
Pear Butter! What
did you do?

08:48.962 --> 08:50.195
I... I'm not sure.

08:55.001 --> 08:56.268
Bright Mac: She
didn't do it, sir.

08:58.204 --> 09:00.671
Excuse me?

09:00.740 --> 09:02.006
The water silo.

09:02.075 --> 09:03.174
It was my fault.

09:07.047 --> 09:09.213
You owe me a
new silo, boy.

09:09.282 --> 09:11.616
And you, come with me.

09:13.119 --> 09:17.154
No daughter of mine is gonna
make goo goo eyes at an Apple.

09:17.223 --> 09:20.225
♪♪

09:25.131 --> 09:26.731
Grand Pear never
would have known

09:26.800 --> 09:28.833
it was your
father's fault!

09:28.902 --> 09:30.668
But there was no way
he'd let your mother

09:30.737 --> 09:32.803
take the blame for
something he did.

09:32.872 --> 09:34.939
So Dad was super honest!

09:35.008 --> 09:37.576
Apple doesn't fall far from
the tree huh, Applejack?

09:38.945 --> 09:41.212
Your dad worked the
apple farm all day

09:41.281 --> 09:43.247
and then headed over to the
Pear's on his breaks

09:43.316 --> 09:44.982
to fix the water silo.

09:45.051 --> 09:46.651
I didn't see him for weeks!

09:46.720 --> 09:47.719
Not that he minded.

09:47.788 --> 09:50.388
Gave him a chance to
get to know your ma.

09:50.457 --> 09:52.223
Did you know our mom, too?

09:52.292 --> 09:54.392
Buttercup was a real
peach of a Pear

09:54.461 --> 09:56.260
but if you want to
know more about her,

09:56.329 --> 09:57.362
you should ask
Mrs. Cake.

09:58.832 --> 09:59.997
Mrs. Cake?

10:00.066 --> 10:01.699
She and your mom
were inseparable

10:01.768 --> 10:03.234
when they were fillies!

10:03.303 --> 10:04.168
Then let's go!

10:04.237 --> 10:05.337
Thanks, Burnt Oak.

10:09.442 --> 10:12.410
Would it be OK if we
stopped by again sometime?

10:12.479 --> 10:14.011
To hear more stories?

10:14.080 --> 10:15.846
I'd like that very much.

10:15.915 --> 10:22.253
♪♪

10:22.322 --> 10:27.091
Well, cinnamon sugar on toast,
all three Apple siblings!

10:27.160 --> 10:28.459
Hi, Mrs. Cake. We heard you

10:28.528 --> 10:30.961
and our ma used
to be real good friends

10:31.030 --> 10:33.264
and we were hoping you could
tell us a bit about her.

10:33.333 --> 10:35.900
Oh, I would love to.

10:35.969 --> 10:38.035
I never knew the right
time to bring it up,

10:38.104 --> 10:40.337
but I'm so glad you came.

10:40.406 --> 10:44.008
For starters, did you all
know that it was your mom

10:44.077 --> 10:46.877
who convinced me
to pursue baking?

10:46.946 --> 10:49.213
But isn't your name Mrs. Cake?

10:49.282 --> 10:50.815
Not always.

10:50.884 --> 10:53.384
Back when I was Chiffon Swirl,

10:53.453 --> 10:56.754
I had no idea what I
was supposed to do.

10:56.823 --> 11:01.025
But one day, your mom brought me
some candied pears, eggs, flour,

11:01.094 --> 11:04.195
sugar and vanilla and told
me to just be creative.

11:04.264 --> 11:05.330
Next thing I knew,

11:05.398 --> 11:07.431
I was whipping up
pear upside-down cake

11:07.500 --> 11:09.767
and I got my cutie mark!

11:09.836 --> 11:11.902
It was like she knew what
I was supposed to do

11:11.971 --> 11:13.804
long before I did.

11:13.873 --> 11:15.773
Just like you, sugarcube!

11:15.842 --> 11:17.975
Or rather, you're
just like her!

11:18.044 --> 11:20.511
That was the first
of many cakes for me

11:20.580 --> 11:23.814
and Buttercup was with
me through it all.

11:23.883 --> 11:25.150
She'd be my taste tester...

11:27.887 --> 11:29.087
help with the
decorating...

11:32.892 --> 11:34.392
and prep new ingredients.

11:36.563 --> 11:39.130
Over the years, I
perfected my recipes.

11:40.834 --> 11:43.367
Your mom did so much for me,

11:43.436 --> 11:46.771
one day I wanted to
surprise her with a cake.

11:46.840 --> 11:51.142
♪♪

11:51.211 --> 11:53.011
[laughter]

11:56.182 --> 11:57.082
[sneeze]

12:00.353 --> 12:02.821
[giggle]

12:06.926 --> 12:07.858
[crack]

12:07.927 --> 12:08.927
[gasp]

12:11.464 --> 12:13.564
Oh, it's just you!

12:13.633 --> 12:14.932
Sorry.

12:15.001 --> 12:17.935
I just brought you a little
something to say thank you...

12:18.004 --> 12:19.504
but I see you're busy.

12:21.074 --> 12:22.540
[giggle]

12:22.609 --> 12:24.109
Promise you won't say anything.

12:31.384 --> 12:34.351
What in tarnation are
you doin', Bright Mac?

12:34.420 --> 12:37.454
We do not fraternize
with Pears!

12:37.523 --> 12:38.923
Ptui!

12:38.992 --> 12:42.993
♪♪

12:43.062 --> 12:45.362
You and Bright Mac?

12:45.431 --> 12:48.432
I wouldn't believe it if I
hadn't seen it with my own eyes.

12:48.501 --> 12:50.968
Your families hate each other!

12:51.037 --> 12:54.872
I can't help it, we
just sort of happened.

12:54.941 --> 12:57.842
<i>Then Pear Butter told me</i>
<i>the sweetest love story</i>

12:57.911 --> 12:59.177
<i>I have ever heard.</i>

13:01.648 --> 13:04.248
Happy one-hundred-and-thirty-one
-thousand-four-hundred-

13:04.317 --> 13:06.451
and-fifty-six-hour
anniversary, Darlin.

13:08.054 --> 13:09.486
What? Ha ha.

13:09.555 --> 13:11.422
That's way longer than
we've been together.

13:11.491 --> 13:13.057
I know.

13:13.126 --> 13:14.592
But it's the anniversary
of the first time

13:14.661 --> 13:16.127
I called you Buttercup.

13:18.164 --> 13:20.231
It's OK if you didn't
get me anything.

13:22.435 --> 13:25.069
Actually, I did.

13:25.138 --> 13:26.904
A guitar? For me?

13:26.973 --> 13:29.540
But I don't know
how to play!

13:29.609 --> 13:31.141
Quiet, you.

13:31.210 --> 13:38.115
♪♪

13:38.184 --> 13:41.552
<i>♪ We're far apart in</i>
<i>every way, ♪</i>

13:41.621 --> 13:45.155
<i>♪ but you're the best</i>
<i>part of my day... ♪</i>

13:45.224 --> 13:48.959
<i>♪ And sure as I</i>
<i>breathe the air, ♪</i>

13:49.028 --> 13:52.196
<i>♪ I know we are the</i>
<i>perfect pair. ♪</i>

13:52.265 --> 13:59.136
<i>♪ On a prickly path that</i>
<i>goes on for miles, ♪</i>

13:59.205 --> 14:06.211
<i>♪ but it's worth it just</i>
<i>to see you smile... ♪</i>

14:06.646 --> 14:10.281
<i>♪ And I cannot</i>
<i>be pulled apart, ♪</i>

14:10.350 --> 14:13.951
<i>♪ from the hold you</i>
<i>have on my heart. ♪</i>

14:14.020 --> 14:18.622
<i>♪ And even if the world</i>
<i>tells us it's wrong, ♪</i>

14:18.691 --> 14:21.558
<i>♪ you're in my head</i>
<i>like a catchy song. ♪</i>

14:21.627 --> 14:23.627
Wow. It's just
... wow.

14:23.696 --> 14:24.595
Do you like it?

14:24.664 --> 14:25.830
Be honest now.

14:25.899 --> 14:27.498
It's the best gift you
could have given me!

14:27.567 --> 14:31.702
<i>♪ Seasons change and</i>
<i>leaves may fall ♪</i>

14:31.771 --> 14:35.339
<i>♪ but I'll be with you</i>
<i>through them all ♪</i>

14:35.408 --> 14:42.246
<i>♪ and rain or shine</i>
<i>you'll always be mine. ♪</i>

14:42.315 --> 14:49.320
<i>♪ On a prickly path that</i>
<i>goes on for miles. ♪</i>

14:49.522 --> 14:56.361
<i>♪ You're the only one who</i>
<i>makes it all worthwhile ♪</i>

14:57.430 --> 15:01.065
<i>♪ and you should not</i>
<i>blame me too ♪</i>

15:01.134 --> 15:04.502
<i>♪ if I can't help fallin'</i>
<i>in love with you. ♪</i>

15:07.573 --> 15:09.373
Hey! No fair!

15:09.442 --> 15:11.742
I was gonna tell
you the same thing!

15:11.811 --> 15:13.478
You're just mad
I beat you to it.

15:15.448 --> 15:16.447
I'm telling ya.

15:16.516 --> 15:19.283
I was gonna pull you
up, cover your eyes,

15:19.352 --> 15:20.385
lead you over here...

15:22.722 --> 15:23.988
and say "surprise!"

15:27.693 --> 15:31.195
And then you'd say,
"Oh, Bright Mac. I love it!"

15:31.264 --> 15:34.098
And then I'd say
"I love you."

15:34.167 --> 15:35.399
Too bad it didn't
work out, though.

15:35.468 --> 15:37.235
Yup. Too bad.

15:40.406 --> 15:42.506
The Pears are moving!

15:42.575 --> 15:43.975
[gasp]

15:48.081 --> 15:49.546
I mean, I figured
the Pears moved

15:49.615 --> 15:51.682
but I didn't know all that
stuff happened before

15:51.751 --> 15:54.084
with Granny and Grand Pear.

15:54.153 --> 15:56.220
It must have been really
hard on our parents.

15:56.289 --> 15:57.322
Oh, it was...

15:58.791 --> 16:00.090
We're moving?

16:00.159 --> 16:01.558
To Van Hoover?

16:01.627 --> 16:03.460
But that's so far!

16:03.529 --> 16:05.429
It's what's best.

16:05.498 --> 16:07.765
There's acres of
untouched land

16:07.834 --> 16:10.100
and a warehouse to
make our jams!

16:10.169 --> 16:12.169
We'll get to expand
our business

16:12.238 --> 16:16.206
and get away from those
gosh darn Apples!

16:16.275 --> 16:18.542
<i>Mrs. Cake: Pear Butter</i>
<i>was devastated.</i>

16:18.611 --> 16:23.080
<i>But seeing no way out of it,</i>
<i>she did what she had to do.</i>

16:23.149 --> 16:24.715
So, that's it?

16:24.784 --> 16:26.583
What do you want me
to do, Bright Mac?

16:26.652 --> 16:27.751
We're moving.

16:27.820 --> 16:31.388
I love you but I have
to stay with my family.

16:31.457 --> 16:34.158
<i>Then Bright Mac did the</i>
<i>most romantic thing</i>

16:34.227 --> 16:36.194
<i>I've ever seen anypony do.</i>

16:37.296 --> 16:39.630
What? What? Tell us!

16:39.699 --> 16:43.300
We're gonna need one more
pony to tell that story.

16:43.369 --> 16:45.469
Mayor Mare, you
knew our parents?

16:45.538 --> 16:47.671
Not as well
as Mrs. Cake,

16:47.740 --> 16:50.174
but I did play a part
in their love story.

16:50.243 --> 16:52.209
The night before the
Pear family moved,

16:52.278 --> 16:54.211
Bright Mac asked
me to meet him

16:54.280 --> 16:56.547
at the edge of Sweet
Apple Acres...

16:59.552 --> 17:00.851
[gasp]

17:00.920 --> 17:03.320
♪♪

17:03.389 --> 17:05.689
I don't want to be
apart from you, ever.

17:05.758 --> 17:09.159
I'm not sure what we'll
do but I'm sure of us.

17:09.228 --> 17:11.129
So sure that I'd
marry you today.

17:12.865 --> 17:14.098
I would too!

17:15.935 --> 17:19.169
I think that's my cue.

17:19.238 --> 17:23.173
<i>I had the honor of officiating</i>
<i>your parents' secret wedding.</i>

17:23.242 --> 17:25.709
<i>And it was perfect.</i>

17:25.778 --> 17:29.279
<i>Bright Mac knew Buttercup</i>
<i>wouldn't want a big splash--</i>

17:29.348 --> 17:31.782
<i>Apple Bloom: Reminds me of</i>
<i>somepony else I know...</i>

17:31.851 --> 17:33.417
<i>Big Mac: Hee hee. Eeeyup.</i>

17:33.486 --> 17:36.154
<i>Mayor Mare: So they had a</i>
<i>special way to seal their vows.</i>

17:38.491 --> 17:39.623
I now pronounce you--

17:39.692 --> 17:40.758
Granny: What is goin' on?

17:40.826 --> 17:42.826
What's with all
these here candles?

17:42.895 --> 17:45.195
Grand Pear: Pear
Butter, where are you?

17:45.264 --> 17:47.331
You're supposed
to be packing!

17:47.400 --> 17:49.400
What are you two doing?

17:52.271 --> 17:54.204
Ma, Grand Pear...

17:54.273 --> 17:55.739
Buttercup and I are in love.

17:55.808 --> 17:57.541
What?

17:57.610 --> 18:00.210
And we'll be married as
soon as Mayor Mare says...

18:00.279 --> 18:02.080
Oh! I now pronounce
you husband and wife.

18:03.549 --> 18:04.781
Doesn't that feel nice.

18:04.850 --> 18:08.185
[kiss]

18:08.254 --> 18:10.387
What are you talkin'
about? Married?

18:10.456 --> 18:12.256
You two can't be married!

18:12.325 --> 18:13.790
Finally something
we can agree on!

18:13.859 --> 18:16.293
Pear Butter, enough
of this nonsense.

18:16.362 --> 18:20.731
We're moving and you gotta
stick with your family.

18:20.800 --> 18:25.169
But... the Apples are
my family now, too.

18:25.238 --> 18:29.339
♪♪

18:29.408 --> 18:30.941
You can't be serious.

18:31.010 --> 18:33.844
Are you choosing
to be an Apple?

18:33.913 --> 18:35.279
Over being a Pear?

18:36.916 --> 18:39.850
Are you making
me choose?

18:39.919 --> 18:41.419
Yes. I am.

18:43.923 --> 18:45.255
Then yeah.

18:45.324 --> 18:46.524
I guess I am.

18:49.962 --> 18:51.695
Fine!

18:51.764 --> 18:54.432
[sobbing]

18:57.737 --> 19:01.672
I can't believe Grand Pear
just up and left Ma like that.

19:01.741 --> 19:04.841
No wonder Granny never
told us about any of this.

19:04.910 --> 19:06.944
These things are never easy.

19:07.013 --> 19:09.813
And it's hard to know
when it is a good time.

19:09.882 --> 19:12.716
It seems to me that
now's as good a time as any.

19:12.785 --> 19:14.885
To talk to both
our grandparents.

19:14.954 --> 19:20.857
♪♪

19:20.926 --> 19:23.493
Apple Bloom: 'Scuse me?
Grand Pear?

19:23.562 --> 19:25.929
I'm Applejack and
this is Big MacIntosh

19:25.998 --> 19:28.298
but you already know
who we are, don't you?

19:28.367 --> 19:30.667
Sure do.

19:30.736 --> 19:33.670
Did you really move to Ponyville
just for a change of pace?

19:33.739 --> 19:35.872
No.

19:35.941 --> 19:38.008
Then you came here
because you're sorry

19:38.077 --> 19:40.711
and you want to get
to know us, too?

19:40.780 --> 19:43.380
I'm so sorry.

19:43.449 --> 19:48.352
I was just so angry,
but I never...

19:48.421 --> 19:49.921
It's in the past, Grand Pear.

19:52.491 --> 19:54.458
Ooh, can I call
you Grandpere Pear?

19:54.527 --> 19:56.393
[chuckle] Sure can!

19:56.462 --> 19:58.895
♪♪

19:58.964 --> 20:00.797
Now where'd you all get to?

20:00.866 --> 20:03.433
I ain't seen hide nor
hair of you's all day.

20:03.502 --> 20:04.735
We've been all over.

20:04.804 --> 20:07.004
Learning about our parents.

20:07.073 --> 20:09.273
Ye have?

20:09.342 --> 20:11.509
And our grandfather.

20:14.947 --> 20:18.615
So you're back, hmmm?

20:18.684 --> 20:20.017
Sure am.

20:20.086 --> 20:23.420
Never should've left.

20:23.489 --> 20:25.956
Finding you and learning all
about Mom and Dad...

20:26.025 --> 20:27.891
I feel like I found
a piece of me

20:27.960 --> 20:29.760
I didn't even
know was missing.

20:29.829 --> 20:33.764
Hearing their story makes me
feel closer to them, somehow.

20:33.833 --> 20:37.668
I'm sorry, I shoulda told
y'all about them sooner.

20:37.737 --> 20:40.370
And I should
have been here.

20:40.439 --> 20:45.642
I can't believe I let a silly
feud keep me from my family.

20:45.711 --> 20:47.644
Nothin's keeping
you from us now.

20:47.713 --> 20:49.880
Let's not miss
anything else.

20:49.949 --> 20:51.948
Applejack's right.

20:52.017 --> 20:55.085
Welcome back, prickly old pear.

20:55.154 --> 20:58.889
Thanks, you old crab apple.

20:58.958 --> 21:00.390
Now that we're
all together,

21:00.459 --> 21:02.025
there's something we
want to show you.

21:02.094 --> 21:04.328
Mom and Dad left us something
to remember them by.

21:04.397 --> 21:05.363
Come on!

21:10.970 --> 21:13.837
Whoa!

21:13.906 --> 21:16.540
It's beautiful!

21:16.609 --> 21:19.109
It's impossible.

21:19.178 --> 21:20.744
♪♪

21:20.813 --> 21:22.546
If anything's
gonna make it through,

21:22.615 --> 21:25.115
it's Apples and Pears.

21:25.184 --> 21:26.650
[chuckle]

21:26.719 --> 21:29.720
♪♪
